Sterling Lord Papers

Contents

Series I: Subject Files

Scope and Content

This series contains the subject files kept by the Sterling Lord Literistic Agency. These files consist of correspondence of agents with authors and publishers. They also contain manuscripts, photographs, promotional material, and all other items associated with the authors being managed by the agency. Subseries A contains the general subject files. These are described at the box level. Subseries B contains subject files that had been removed by the agency, grouping the materials of specific authors together. There is still material from these authors in the general subject files.

Subseries A: General

Scope and Content

This subseries contains the general subject files from the Sterling Lord Archive. It includes correspondence files with authors, publishers, and agents, and other general subject files kept by Sterling Lord and other agents at the Sterling Lord Literistic Agency.

Series II: Financial, Administrative, and Legal

Scope and Content

This series contains all financial, administrative and legal papers from Sterling Lord and the Sterling Lord Literistic Agency. Subseries A, the administrative and legal files, contain contracts, personnel files, and other material relating to the administration of the agency. Subseries B, the financial files, contains bank statements, cancelled checks, royalty statements, budget reports, and all other financial material.

Subseries A: Administrative and Legal papers

Scope and Content

This series contains the administrative and legal papers from the Sterling Lord Literistic Agency. It includes contracts for films and merchandising, legal correspondence and case files, calendars, log books, and all other material related to the administration of the agency.

Arrangement

Several of the files in this series had ID numbers with the folder titles [STER-xxx]. There was no apparent order to these numbers. The folders have been arranged alphabetically, but the ID numbers have been maintained in the title.
